Key Match Events: Adam Zampa bowled Australia to a 33-run victory
Chris Woakes removed both the Australia openers
Marnus Labuschagne (71) rebuilt the innings in the company of Steve Smith (44)
Adil Rashid dismissed Smith and Josh Inglis in his successive overs
Cameron Green (47) and Marcus Stoinis (35) scored some quick runs
David Warner took the catch to dismiss England's Moeen Ali, off the bowling of Adam Zampa
Stokes smashed three sixes but England's title defence was effectively over when he swept Zampa to Stoinis at short fine leg in the 36th over
Post-Match Reflections: Buttler did not spare himself in his blunt assessment of their performance in the showpiece event
Buttler said the players had let down themselves as well as their fans
Buttler said the players had let down themselves as well as their fans. 'To be stood in this position having arrived in India with high hopes is incredibly tough and disappointing. It hurts a lot.'

In what was unthinkable at the start of the tournament, England, who face the Netherlands and Pakistan in their remaining matches, are now fighting for a top-eight finish in order to qualify for the 2025 Champions Trophy in Pakistan.
Miscellaneous Highlights: England's stuttering title defence at the 50-over Cricket World Cup has officially crumbled
Others: Adam Zampa was player of the match for his stellar bowling that included the prized wickets of Buttler, Stokes and Moeen.
